<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1138">
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate, Ciudad
                                    Juárez</hi></placeName>,<lb/>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-20">undated</date>] (<hi rend="italic">Received August 20, 1912—11.45
                                p.m.</hi>)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Federals occupied Juárez to-day. Civil government to be established
                            to-morrow and railroad traffic resumed. General belief that revolution
                            is ended in State of Chihuahua; refugees will now return to their homes.
                            General rejoicing.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>